WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.225
Welcome to a quick update on Jacob's weekly tracker configuration.

00:00:04.225 --> 00:00:08.451
As of April eleventh, twenty twenty six, the weekly tracker

00:00:08.451 --> 00:00:12.676
now watches six topics instead of four. Here's what's on

00:00:12.676 --> 00:00:16.901
the list and why. Quick context. The weekly tracker is

00:00:16.901 --> 00:00:21.127
a scheduled task that runs every Friday at seven p.m.

00:00:21.127 --> 00:00:25.352
Central. It reads a single page in Jacob's Obsidian vault

00:00:25.352 --> 00:00:29.577
called Tracked Topics, iterates through each active topic, searches the

00:00:29.577 --> 00:00:33.803
web, Reddit, prediction markets, and news sources for new developments,

00:00:33.803 --> 00:00:38.028
and then appends updates to the relevant vault pages. Yesterday

00:00:38.028 --> 00:00:42.254
we moved the topic list out of the task prompt

00:00:42.254 --> 00:00:46.479
and into the vault so any Claude instance, or Jacob

00:00:46.479 --> 00:00:50.704
himself, can edit it directly. Today we added two new

00:00:50.704 --> 00:00:54.930
topics based on a vault-wide search. Topic one is Anthropic's

00:00:54.930 --> 00:00:59.155
Mythos model release. This has been the flagship topic for

00:00:59.155 --> 00:01:03.380
weeks. The tracker watches for leaked release dates, pricing signals,

00:01:03.380 --> 00:01:07.606
benchmark rumors, Project Glasswing developments, and any movement on whether

00:01:07.606 --> 00:01:11.831
a public variant ships. It monitors r slash Anthropic, r

00:01:11.831 --> 00:01:16.056
slash Claude A-I, r slash singularity, r slash Local Llama,

00:01:16.056 --> 00:01:20.282
and checks Manifold for Mythos release probability markets. Topic two

00:01:20.282 --> 00:01:24.507
is the Jefferson City Riverfront Connector Bridge and BUILD grant.

00:01:24.507 --> 00:01:28.732
This tracks the Reconnecting Jefferson City infrastructure project, the High

00:01:28.732 --> 00:01:32.958
Street Viaduct replacement, the roughly twenty five million dollar BUILD

00:01:32.958 --> 00:01:37.183
grant application with a decision expected this summer, city council

00:01:37.183 --> 00:01:41.408
votes, MoDOT updates, and the status of HB twenty one

00:01:41.408 --> 00:01:45.634
oh eight. Topic three is Jefferson City local government more

00:01:45.634 --> 00:01:49.859
broadly. City council meetings, Cole County commission actions, Jefferson City

00:01:49.859 --> 00:01:54.085
Public Schools board decisions, local elections, zoning, and major development

00:01:54.085 --> 00:01:58.310
projects. The update log is append only, most recent first.

00:01:58.310 --> 00:02:02.535
Topic four is the Pebble Index oh one smartwatch. Production

00:02:02.535 --> 00:02:06.761
status, shipping timeline, firmware updates, and community reviews. Pebble Time

00:02:06.761 --> 00:02:10.986
two is a leading indicator since it ships before Index

00:02:10.986 --> 00:02:15.211
oh one. Now for the two new topics. Topic five

00:02:15.211 --> 00:02:19.437
is Apple rumors and news. Jacob's vault has a massive

00:02:19.437 --> 00:02:23.662
Apple topics folder with years of WWDC notes, device timeline

00:02:23.662 --> 00:02:27.887
tracking, Apple Intelligence analysis, and detailed opinions on the ecosystem.

00:02:27.887 --> 00:02:32.113
The tracker will now surface meaningful Apple product, software, and

00:02:32.113 --> 00:02:36.338
ecosystem news, filtering aggressively to only the items that would

00:02:36.338 --> 00:02:40.563
actually affect Jacob's decisions or represent a real strategic shift.

00:02:40.563 --> 00:02:44.789
That means new device rumors, Apple Intelligence developments, OS releases

00:02:44.789 --> 00:02:49.014
across i-O-S, i-Pad-O-S, mac-O-S, watch-O-S, and vision-O-S, WWDC announcements, Siri

00:02:49.014 --> 00:02:53.239
strategy shifts, and Mark Gurman scoops. The primary sources are

00:02:53.239 --> 00:02:57.465
nine to five Mac, Mac Rumors, Bloomberg's Power On newsletter,

00:02:57.465 --> 00:03:01.690
Six Colors, and Daring Fireball. Gurman's Sunday Power On is

00:03:01.690 --> 00:03:05.915
the single most valuable source and gets checked first each

00:03:05.915 --> 00:03:10.141
run. When Apple Watch Ultra four news appears, it cross-posts

00:03:10.141 --> 00:03:14.366
into the wearables tracker because that device is central to

00:03:14.366 --> 00:03:18.592
Jacob's switching decision. Topic six is Whoop and the wearables

00:03:18.592 --> 00:03:22.817
ecosystem. This one is driven directly by the Core Question

00:03:22.817 --> 00:03:27.042
at the top of Jacob's Wearables Watch note: should he

00:03:27.042 --> 00:03:31.268
switch from Apple Watch to Whoop, or wait for the

00:03:31.268 --> 00:03:35.493
Ultra four in September? The tracker watches Whoop membership and

00:03:35.493 --> 00:03:39.718
product changes, new features, algorithm updates, Oura Ring five rumors,

00:03:39.718 --> 00:03:43.944
Garmin's CIRQA smart band, validation studies comparing consumer wearables to

00:03:43.944 --> 00:03:48.169
E-C-G, and commentary from the quantified-self and endurance running communities.

00:03:48.169 --> 00:03:52.394
Sources include D-C Rainmaker, The Quantified Scientist, Wareable, and PubMed

00:03:52.394 --> 00:03:56.620
for validation research. The working verdict right now is to

00:03:56.620 --> 00:04:00.845
wait for the Apple Watch Ultra four before making any

00:04:00.845 --> 00:04:05.070
switch. If new evidence would materially shift that verdict, the

00:04:05.070 --> 00:04:09.296
weekly summary will flag it explicitly rather than quietly updating

00:04:09.296 --> 00:04:13.521
the note. That's the full list. Six topics, one config

00:04:13.521 --> 00:04:17.746
file, one scheduled task. The config lives at one dash

00:04:17.746 --> 00:04:21.972
Projects slash Weekly Tracker Updates slash Tracked Topics dot M-D.

00:04:21.972 --> 00:04:26.197
To add a new topic, copy the template block at

00:04:26.197 --> 00:04:30.423
